========================
CODE SNIPPETS
========================
TITLE: React-Admin Data Fetching Hooks
DESCRIPTION: This section details various hooks provided by react-admin for interacting with data providers. These hooks abstract the complexities of API calls, allowing developers to easily fetch, create, update, and delete data. They are essential for building dynamic and data-bound user interfaces.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/navigation.html#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useGetList } from 'react-admin';

function MyListComponent() {
  const { data, isLoading, error } = useGetList('posts');
  // ... render logic
}
```

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useCreate } from 'react-admin';

function MyCreateComponent() {
  const [create, { data, isLoading, error }] = useCreate('posts');
  // ... form submission logic
}
```

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useUpdateMany } from 'react-admin';

function MyUpdateComponent() {
  const [updateMany] = useUpdateMany('posts', [{ id: 1, data: { status: 'published' } }]);
  // ... update logic
}
```

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useDeleteMany } from 'react-admin';

function MyDeleteComponent() {
  const [deleteMany] = useDeleteMany('posts', [1, 2, 3]);
  // ... delete logic
}
```

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useDataProvider } from 'react-admin';

function MyDataProviderComponent() {
  const dataProvider = useDataProvider();
  // ... use dataProvider directly
}
```

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { fetchJson } from 'react-admin';

async function fetchData() {
  const response = await fetchJson('/api/data');
  // ... process response
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Use Get List Hook - React Admin
DESCRIPTION: The `useGetList` hook fetches a list of resources from the data provider. It handles pagination, sorting, and filtering, returning the data and associated metadata.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/Reference.md#_snippet_91

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { useGetList } from './useGetList';

const PostList = () => {
  const { data, isLoading, error } = useGetList('posts', {
    pagination: { page: 1, perPage: 10 },
    sort: { field: 'title', order: 'ASC' },
    filter: { published: true },
  });

  if (isLoading) return <p>Loading posts...</p>;
  if (error) return <p>Error: {error.message}</p>;

  return (
    <ul>
      {data.map(post => (
        <li key={post.id}>{post.title}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
};
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Fetch List using useGetList Hook in React-admin
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the `useGetList` hook within a React component to fetch data. This hook abstracts data fetching logic, handling loading and error states, and providing data and total count.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/Architecture.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useGetList } from 'react-admin';

const MyComponent = () => {
    const { data, total, loading, error } = useGetList('posts', {
        pagination: { page: 1, perPage: 5 },
        sort: { field: 'title', order: 'ASC' },
        filter: { author_id: 12 },
    });

    if (loading) return <Loading />;
    if (error) return <Error />;
    return (
        <div>
            <h1>Found {total} posts matching your query</h1>
            <ul>
                {data.map(record => (
                    <li key={record.id}>{record.title}</li>
                ))}
            </ul>
        </div>
    )
};
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: React-Admin CRM: Custom Chart in Dashboard
DESCRIPTION: Integrates a custom d3.js or Nivo chart into the react-admin dashboard to visualize CRM data, such as deals progression.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/Demos.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import * as React from "react";
import { Card, CardContent, Typography } from '@mui/material';
import { useQuery } from 'react-query';
import { fetchUtils } from 'react-admin';
import { ResponsiveLine } from '@nivo/line';

const DealsChart = () => {
    const { data, isLoading } = useQuery(['dealsChart'], () =>
        fetchUtils.fetchJson('/deals?filter={}') // Replace with actual API endpoint
    );

    if (isLoading) {
        return <p>Loading chart...</p>;
    }

    // Format data for Nivo chart
    const formattedData = [
        {
            id: 'deals',
            color: 'hsl(210, 70%, 50%)',
            data: data.map(deal => ({ x: deal.date, y: deal.value }))
        }
    ];

    return (
        <Card>
            <CardContent>
                <Typography variant="h6" gutterBottom>Deals Pipeline</Typography>
                <div style={{ height: 300 }}>
                    <ResponsiveLine
                        data={formattedData}
                        margin={{ top: 50, right: 50, bottom: 50, left: 60 }}
                        xScale={{ type: 'time', format: '%Y-%m-%d' }}
                        yScale={{ type: 'linear', min: 0, max: 'auto', stacked: false, reverse: false }}
                        axisTop={null}
                        axisRight={null}
                        axisBottom={{
                            format: '%Y-%m-%d',
                            tickRotation: 45,
                        }}
                        axisLeft={{
                            tickSize: 5,
                            tickPadding: 5,
                            tickRotation: 0,
                            legend: 'Value',
                            legendOffset: -40,
                            legendPosition: 'middle'
                        }}
                        enableGridX={false}
                        colors={{ scheme: 'nivo' }}
                        pointSize={10}
                        pointLabel={(d) => d.yFormatted}
                        pointLabelYOffset={-12}
                        useMesh={true}
                    />
                </div>
            </CardContent>
        </Card>
    );
};

export default DealsChart;
```

