TITLE: Fetch Single User Record with useGetOne Hook
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates fetching a single user record using the `useGetOne` hook, which simplifies data fetching and state management. It returns data, loading status, and error information.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/Actions.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useGetOne } from 'react-admin';
import { Loading, Error } from './MyComponents';

const UserProfile = ({ userId }) => {
    const { isPending, error, data: user } = useGetOne('users', { id: userId });

    if (isPending) return <Loading />;
    if (error) return <Error />;
    if (!user) return null;

    return (
        <ul>
            <li>Name: {user.name}</li>
            <li>Email: {user.email}</li>
        </ul>
    )
};

```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: React-Admin Common Hooks
DESCRIPTION: Commonly used hooks in react-admin for data fetching, notifications, and redirection. These hooks simplify common UI patterns and state management.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/navigation.html#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { useNotify, useRedirect, useRefresh } from 'react-admin';

const MyComponent = () => {
    const notify = useNotify();
    const redirect = useRedirect();
    const refresh = useRefresh();

    const handleClick = () => {
        notify('Action successful!');
        redirect('/users');
        refresh();
    };

    return <button onClick={handleClick}>Perform Action</button>;
};
```

