TITLE: Use List Controller Hook - React Admin
DESCRIPTION: The `useListController` hook manages the state and logic for a list view. It handles data fetching, pagination, sorting, filtering, and selection, simplifying the creation of list components.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/Reference.md#_snippet_102

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { useListController } from './useListController';

const ListView = (props) => {
  const controllerProps = useListController(props);

  return (
    <div>
      {/* Render list components using controllerProps */}
      <p>List View Controller</p>
    </div>
  );
};
```

