TITLE: Use useGetListLive Hook in React-Admin
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the useGetListLive hook to fetch and display a list of posts with live updates. It handles loading and error states, and maps the fetched data to list items. This hook subscribes to resource updates.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useGetListLive.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useGetListLive } from '@react-admin/ra-realtime';

const LatestNews = () => {
    const { data, total, isPending, error } = useGetListLive('posts', {
        pagination: { page: 1, perPage: 10 },
        sort: { field: 'published_at', order: 'DESC' },
    });
    if (isPending) {
        return <Loading />;
    }
    if (error) {
        return <p>ERROR</p>;
    }

    return (
        <ul>
            {data.map(item => (
                <li key={item.id}>{item.title}</li>
            ))}
        </ul>
    );
