TITLE: Control Fetching with Options (e.g., enabled)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to use the `options` parameter in `useInfiniteGetList` to control the hook's behavior, such as conditionally enabling the data fetching based on a user ID.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useInfiniteGetList.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const { data } = useInfiniteGetList(
    'posts', 
    {
        pagination: { page: 1, perPage: 25 }, 
        sort: { field: 'published_at', order: 'DESC' },
        filter: { user_id: user && user.id },
    },
    { enabled: !!user }
);

```

