TITLE: Implement List Controller Logic with useListController
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the `useListController` hook to manage the data fetching, filtering, and pagination state for a list view in react-admin. It replaces manual state management with a hook that provides context for child components like `<ListContextProvider>`.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/ListTutorial.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import {
    Title,
    useListController,
    DataTable,
    ListContextProvider,
    FilterForm,
    Pagination,
    TextInput
} from 'react-admin';
import { Card } from '@mui/material';

const BookList = () => {
    const listContext = useListController();
    if (listContext.isPending) {
        return <div>Loading...</div>;
    }
    const filters = [<TextInput label="Search" source="q" size="small" alwaysOn />];
    return (
        <ListContextProvider value={listContext}>
            <div>
                <Title title="Book list" />
                <FilterForm filters={filters} />
                <Card>
                    <DataTable>
                        <DataTable.Col source="id" />
                        <DataTable.Col source="title" />
                        <DataTable.Col source="author" />
                        <DataTable.Col source="year" />
                    </DataTable>
                </Card>
                <Pagination />
            </div>
        </ListContextProvider>
    );
};
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Fetch Related Records with useGetManyReference
DESCRIPTION: This hook fetches a list of records related to a specific record using the data provider's `getManyReference` method. It supports pagination, sorting, and filtering, returning data, total count, loading state, and error information.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useGetManyReference.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useGetManyReference, useRecordContext } from 'react-admin';

const PostComments = () => {
    const record = useRecordContext();
    // fetch all comments related to the current record
    const { data, isPending, error } = useGetManyReference(
        'comments',
        {
            target: 'post_id',
            id: record.id,
