TITLE: Fetching User Profile with useDataProvider
DESCRIPTION: An example of using useDataProvider within a React component to fetch and display a user's profile data, including loading and error states.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useDataProvider.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { useDataProvider } from 'react-admin';
import { Loading, Error } from './MyComponents';

const UserProfile = ({ userId }) => {
    const dataProvider = useDataProvider();
    const [user, setUser] = useState();
    const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
    const [error, setError] = useState();
    useEffect(() => {
        dataProvider.getOne('users', { id: userId })
            .then(({ data }) => {
                setUser(data);
                setLoading(false);
            })
            .catch(error => {
                setError(error);
                setLoading(false);
            })
    }, []);

    if (loading) return <Loading />;
    if (error) return <Error />;
    if (!user) return null;

    return (
        <ul>
            <li>Name: {user.name}</li>
            <li>Email: {user.email}</li>
        </ul>
    )
};
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Access DataProvider Directly with useDataProvider
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to access the react-admin DataProvider instance directly using the `useDataProvider` hook. This allows for custom data manipulation, such as updating a user's banned status.

SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/DataFetchingGuide.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useDataProvider } from 'react-admin';

const BanUserButton = ({ userId }) => {
    const dataProvider = useDataProvider();
    const handleClick = () => {
        dataProvider.update('users', { id: userId, data: { isBanned: true } });
    };
    return <Button label="Ban user" onClick={handleClick} />;
};

```

========================
QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS
========================
TOPIC: useGetList - react-admin
Q: What functionalities does the `useGetList` hook support for fetching data?
A: The `useGetList` hook supports filtering, sorting, and pagination when fetching data. It allows you to specify parameters for these functionalities to customize the data retrieval.


SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useGetList.md#_qa_1

----------------------------------------

TOPIC: useGetList - react-admin
Q: How can the `useGetList` hook be used to display data in react-admin iterator components?
A: To use data fetched by `useGetList` in react-admin iterator components like `<DataTable>` or `<SimpleList>`, you must first create a `ListContext` using the `useList` hook with the fetched data.


SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useGetList.md#_qa_5

----------------------------------------

TOPIC: useGetTree - react-admin
Q: How does the `useGetTree` hook fetch data?
A: The `useGetTree` hook calls the `dataProvider.getTree()` method when the component mounts. This method is specifically supported by the `ra-tree` package for retrieving tree data.


SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useGetTree.md#_qa_1

----------------------------------------

TOPIC: Querying the API with React-Admin
Q: Which react-admin hooks are available for querying data from the API?
A: React-admin provides specific query hooks for each DataProvider read method, including `useGetList`, `useGetOne`, `useGetMany`, and `useGetManyReference`.


SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/Actions.md#_qa_4

----------------------------------------

TOPIC: useChoicesContext - react-admin
Q: What information does the `useChoicesContext` hook provide regarding data fetching in react-admin?
A: The hook provides `isFetching` (true while data is being fetched), `isLoading` (true until data is fetched for the first time), `isPending` (true until data is available for the first time), and an `error` object if any fetching errors occur.


SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useChoicesContext.md#_qa_4

----------------------------------------

TOPIC: Querying the API with React-Admin
Q: What is the recommended approach for fetching data on component mount in react-admin?
A: For fetching data on component mount, it is recommended to use react-admin's query hooks like `useGetOne` or `useGetList`, as they are designed to execute automatically when the component mounts and handle the associated loading and error states.


SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/Actions.md#_qa_7

----------------------------------------

TOPIC: useGetIdentity - react-admin
Q: What underlying hook does `useGetIdentity` utilize in react-admin for data fetching?
A: The `useGetIdentity` hook in react-admin utilizes react-query's `useQuery` hook to call the `authProvider` and manage the data fetching process.


SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useGetIdentity.md#_qa_3

----------------------------------------

TOPIC: Querying the API with React-Admin
Q: What are the benefits of using react-admin's query hooks over directly calling the DataProvider?
A: Using react-admin's query hooks offers several advantages over direct DataProvider calls. They are easier to use, more robust, automatically manage the loading state, and provide better type safety, especially when using TypeScript.


SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/Actions.md#_qa_3

----------------------------------------

TOPIC: useGetList - react-admin
Q: What information is returned by the `useGetList` hook?
A: The `useGetList` hook returns `data` (the fetched records), `total` (the total number of records available), `isPending` (a boolean indicating if the data is being fetched), `error` (any error that occurred during fetching), `refetch` (a function to manually refetch data), and `meta` (metadata from the data provider).


SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useGetList.md#_qa_8

----------------------------------------

TOPIC: useGetListLive - react-admin
Q: What are the key return values from the `useGetListLive` hook?
A: The `useGetListLive` hook returns `data` (the list of records), `total` (the total number of records), `isPending` (a boolean indicating if data is being fetched), and `error` (any error that occurred during fetching).


SOURCE: https://github.com/marmelab/react-admin/blob/master/docs/useGetListLive.md#_qa_3

